#. Tag: title
#: guides.docbook:43
#, no-c-format
msgid "Detailed Guides"
msgstr "Üksikasjalikud juhised"

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:45
#, no-c-format
msgid "This chapter describes how to perform some common tasks in &stage;."
msgstr ""
"See peatükk kirjeldab, kuidas sooritada &stage;'is mõningaid levinumaid "
"ülesandeid."

#. Tag: title
#: guides.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create a &HTML; Slideshow"
msgstr "&HTML;-slaidiseansi loomine"

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:51
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Turn an existing presentation into standard &HTML; pages with accompanying "
"navigation aids."
msgstr ""
"Vaatame, kuidas muuta olemasolev esitlus standardseteks &HTML;-lehekülgedeks "
"koos vajalike liikumisvõimalustega."

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:54
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First, either make a new presentation, or open an existing one. Then, click "
"on <menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>Export as HTML...</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>"
msgstr ""
"Kõigepealt tuleb luua uus esitlus või avada mõni olemasolev. Seejärel tuleb "
"valida menüükäsk <menuchoice><guimenu>Fail</guimenu><guimenuitem>Ekspordi "
"HTML-ina</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "You will then get a dialog box asking for a few details:"
msgstr "Seejärel ilmub dialoog, kus saab paika panna üksikasjad:"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: guides.docbook:60
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Fill in the details for your &HTML; slideshow</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>&HTML;-slaidiseansi üksikasjade määramine</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: guides.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Fill in the details for your &HTML; slideshow</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>&HTML;-slaidiseansi üksikasjade määramine</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Fill in <guilabel>Title</guilabel> and <guilabel>Author</guilabel> fields. "
"Select the slides which should be exported. If you want to change a name "
"used on the &HTML; page for each slide double click on the name and edit it "
"inline."
msgstr ""
"Täida väljad <guilabel>Pealkiri</guilabel> ja <guilabel>Autor</guilabel>. "
"Vali slaidid, mida soovid eksportida. Kui tahad muuta nime, mida kasutatakse "
"iga slaidi &HTML;-leheküljel, tee nimel topeltklõps ja muuda seda sealsamas."

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:76
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <guilabel>Output preview</guilabel> area the downsized slides are "
"displayed and you can check the correct slide order and browse the "
"presentation with the <guiicon>&lt;</guiicon> and <guiicon>&gt;</guiicon> "
"buttons."
msgstr ""
"<guilabel>Väljundi eelvaate</guilabel> alas näeb slaide vähendatud kujul, "
"samuti saab seal kontrollida slaidide järjekorda ja vaadelda esitlust, "
"kasutades nuppe <guiicon>&lt;</guiicon> ja <guiicon>&gt;</guiicon>."

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you can select a stylesheet with the configuration of the &HTML; options."
msgstr "Nüüd saab valida &HTML;-i seadistuste all valida laaditabeli."

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To actually produce your &HTML; presentation, press the <guibutton>Export</"
"guibutton> button and select a folder."
msgstr ""
"Oma &HTML;-esitluse tegelikuks loomiseks tuleb veel vajutada nuppu "
"<guibutton>Ekspordi</guibutton> ja valida kataloog."

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:86
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"What we now have are the newly-produced <filename>html/</filename> and "
"<filename>pics/</filename> folders, created where we earlier set the path:"
msgstr ""
"Nüüd on meil olemas uued kataloogid <filename>html/</filename> ja "
"<filename>pics/</filename> just dialoogis määratud asukohas."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: guides.docbook:91
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>The newly created &HTML; slideshow folders</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Äsja loodud &HTML;-slaidiseansi kataloogid</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: guides.docbook:97
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>The newly created &HTML; slideshow folders</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Äsja loodud &HTML;-slaidiseansi kataloogid</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:102
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There is also an <filename>index.html</filename> file to launch your web "
"slideshow."
msgstr ""
"Veebi-slaidiseansi käivitamiseks on loodud ka fail <filename>index.html</"
"filename>."

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:105
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can see how it works by using your file manager or web browser to open "
"the <filename>index.html</filename> file. Click where prompted, and the "
"first slide of your presentation is displayed. It will now behave as a "
"&stage; slideshow."
msgstr ""
"Seda, kuidas asi välja näeb, saab vaadata, kui avada failihalduri või "
"veebilehitsejaga fail <filename>index.html</filename>. Klõpsa seal, kus seda "
"soovitatakse teha, ning nähtavale ilmub esitluse esimene leht. Edasi käib "
"kõik sarnaselt &stage;'i slaidiseansile."

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each click on the arrow icons take you to the next or previous slide. To get "
"back to the start of the slideshow click on the slide icon."
msgstr ""
"Iga klõps nooleikoonidele viib kas järgmise või eelmise slaidi juurde. "
"Slaidiseansi algusse liikumiseks klõpsa slaidiikoonile."

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:113
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To share your presentation with the world, transfer the newly-produced files "
"to a network-accessible location (&ie; webspace), remembering to keep the "
"folder structure intact."
msgstr ""
"Oma esitluse jagamiseks ülejäänud maailmaga paiguta loodud failid mõnda "
"võrgu kaudu kättesaadavasse asukohta (&ie; veebiruumi). Jälgi, et sa ei "
"muudaks kataloogistruktuuri."

#. Tag: title
#: guides.docbook:119
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating &stage; Templates"
msgstr "&stage;'i mallide loomine"

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:121
#, no-c-format
msgid "It is very easy to create a new template for &stage;."
msgstr "&stage;'i mallide loomine on tegelikult imelihtne."

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:123
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have made a presentation in a style that you would like to use again, "
"you can save it as a template."
msgstr ""
"Kui oled loonud esitluse, mille stiili soovid ka edaspidi kasutada, võid "
"selle salvestada mallina."

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid "This tutorial will show how we can make a new template and save it."
msgstr "Selles osas selgitame, kuidas luua uus mall ja see salvestada."

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid "Open &stage; and create a new document."
msgstr "Ava &stage; ja loo uus dokument."

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To add a little sparkle to the blank slide, we can change the slide "
"background - do this by selecting the <guilabel>Document background</"
"guilabel> tool in the Tools docker."
msgstr ""
"Tühjale slaidile veidi sära lisamiseks muudame slaidi tausta. Seda saab teha "
"tööriistadokis <guilabel>dokumendi tausta</guilabel> tööriista valides."

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:135
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We want the background to look attractive, so you may choose to use an image "
"as a background by clicking the <guibutton>Set image</guibutton> button: "
"feel free to experiment, but keep it beautiful!"
msgstr ""
"Tahame, et meie taust oleks veidi külgetõmbavam, nii et selleks võib valida "
"mõne pildi, klõpsates nupule <guibutton>Määra pilt</guibutton>: "
"eksperimenteeri kuidas tahad, peaasi, et asi ilus välja näeks!"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: guides.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Choosing a slide background</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Slaidi tausta valimine</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: guides.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Choosing a slide background</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Slaidi tausta valimine</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The page should now have the background you desire. Create a text box, and "
"type a heading for your slide:"
msgstr ""
"Leht ilutseb nüüd valitud värvides. Loo tekstikast ja kirjuta sinna oma "
"slaidi pealkiri:"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: guides.docbook:153
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Adding a Heading to the new template</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Pealkirja lisamine uuele mallile</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: guides.docbook:158
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Adding a Heading to the new template</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Pealkirja lisamine uuele mallile</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: guides.docbook:162
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you are happy with your template, go to <menuchoice><guimenu>File</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Save As</guimenuitem></menuchoice> and select "
"<guilabel>Opendocument Presentation Template</guilabel> filetype in the file "
"dialog."
msgstr ""
"Kui mall sind rahuldab, vali menüükäsk <menuchoice><guimenu>Fail</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Salvesta kui</guimenuitem></menuchoice> ning vali "
"failidialoogis failitüübiks <guilabel>Opendocument esitluse mall</guilabel>."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "<screeninfo>File menu option to <guimenuitem>Create HTML Slideshow...</"
#~ "guimenuitem></screeninfo>"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "<screeninfo>Menüü Fail käsk <guilabel>Loo HTML-slaidiseanss...</"
#~ "guilabel></screeninfo>"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "<phrase>File menu option to <guimenuitem>Create HTML Slideshow...</"
#~ "guimenuitem></phrase>"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "<phrase>Menüü Fail käsk <guilabel>Loo HTML-slaidiseanss...</guilabel></"
#~ "phrase>"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "A dialog box asks if you want to use a previously saved configuration:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Ilmuv dialoog pärib, kas soovid kasutada varem salvestatud seadistusi:"

#~ msgid "<screeninfo>Previous configuration dialog</screeninfo>"
#~ msgstr "<screeninfo>Varasemate seadistuste dialoog</screeninfo>"

#~ msgid "<phrase>Previous configuration dialog</phrase>"
#~ msgstr "<phrase>Varasemate seadistuste dialoog</phrase>"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Click <guibutton>No</guibutton> if this is the first time that you have "
#~ "used this feature, or if you want to alter specific options. The "
#~ "<guibutton>Yes</guibutton> option allows you to use details that you have "
#~ "previously entered for your <acronym>HTML</acronym> slideshow, so that "
#~ "you can quickly create the slideshow without needing to adjust the "
#~ "options."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Klõpsa nupule <guibutton>Ei</guibutton>, kui see on sul esimene kord "
#~ "sellist võimalust kasutada. Klõps nupule <guibutton>Jah</guibutton> "
#~ "võimaldab kasutada üksikasju, mida oled varem määranud <acronym>HTML</"
#~ "acronym>-slaidiseansi jaoks."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Fill in each field (the dialog takes the informations from "
#~ "&kcontrolcenter; if they exist) and ensure that the path details are "
#~ "correct, as this is where &kpresenter; will save your new <acronym>HTML</"
#~ "acronym> files and pictures. Click on the <guibutton>Next</guibutton> "
#~ "when you are done."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Täida kõik väljad (dialoog hangib infot &juhtimiskeskus;est, kui seal "
#~ "seda leidub) ja kontrolli, et oled asukoha õigesti valinud, sest just "
#~ "sinna salvestab &kpresenter; loodavad <acronym>HTML</acronym>-failid ja "
#~ "pildid. Klõpsa nupule <guibutton>Edasi</guibutton>, kui oled väljad "
#~ "täitnud."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "If the path you select at this stage does not exist, &kpresenter; will "
#~ "ask if you would like to create it."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Kui valitud asukohta ei ole olemas, küsib &kpresenter;, kas soovid selle "
#~ "luua."

#~ msgid "Now you can configure the specific <acronym>HTML</acronym> options:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Nüüd saad kindlaks määrata spetsiifilisemad <acronym>HTML</acronym>-i "
#~ "valikud:"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "<screeninfo>Fill in additional details for your <acronym>HTML</acronym> "
#~ "slideshow</screeninfo>"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "<screeninfo><acronym>HTML</acronym>-slaidiseansi lisadetailide määramine</"
#~ "screeninfo>"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "<phrase>Fill in additional details for your <acronym>HTML</acronym> "
#~ "slideshow</phrase>"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "<phrase><acronym>HTML</acronym>-slaidiseansi lisadetailide määramine</"
#~ "phrase>"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Here, the encoding and format details can be changed, along with the zoom "
#~ "level of the slides. For example, if you originally designed your slides "
#~ "to display full screen on a 1280 x 1024 resolution screen, you could "
#~ "scale the slides to 50% to enable them to be easily viewed in a much "
#~ "smaller web browser window."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Siin saab määrata slaidide kodeeringu ja vormingu, samuti nende "
#~ "suurenduse. See tähendab, et kui sa näiteks algul lõid slaidid "
#~ "näitamiseks 1280 x 1024 LCD monitori täisekraanil, siis siin saad slaide "
#~ "skaleerida 50% peale, et need oleks korrektselt näha ka märksa väiksemas "
#~ "veebilehitseja aknas."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "In most cases, the defaults will be fine, and you can safely press the "
#~ "<guibutton>Next</guibutton> to continue to the next page."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Enamasti peaks vaikeväärtused olema igati kohased ning sa võid suunduda "
#~ "järgmisele leheküljele, klõpsates nupule <guibutton>Edasi</guibutton>."

#~ msgid "Now you can customize the colors of the web pages:"
#~ msgstr "Siin saab määrata veebilehekülgede värvi:"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "<screeninfo>Setting up the display style for your <acronym>HTML</acronym> "
#~ "slideshow</screeninfo>"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "<screeninfo><acronym>HTML</acronym>-slaidiseansi väljanägemise määramine</"
#~ "screeninfo>"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "<phrase>Setting up the display style for your <acronym>HTML</acronym> "
#~ "slideshow</phrase>"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "<phrase><acronym>HTML</acronym>-slaidiseansi väljanägemise määramine</"
#~ "phrase>"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "When &kpresenter; creates the web pages for you, the text colors for the "
#~ "navigation aids will follow whatever you set here. To change any of these "
#~ "colors, click the colored bar next to the corresponding text label. The "
#~ "colors used in your actual slides will be unchanged."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Kui &kpresenter; veebileheküljed loob, kasutatakse siin määratud värvi "
#~ "slaidide liikumisvõimaluste teksti näitamiseks. Värvi muutmiseks klõpsa "
#~ "vastava kirje juures asuvale värviribale. Slaidide enda värvi siin muuta "
#~ "ei saa."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Choose colors that are complementary to the contents of your presentation."
#~ msgstr "Vali värvid, mis täiendaksid kenasti sinu olemasolevat esitlust."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "The <guibutton>Next</guibutton> button presents a dialog box that allows "
#~ "you to change the name used on the <acronym>HTML</acronym> page for each "
#~ "slide:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Klõps nupule <guibutton>Edasi</guibutton> avab dialoogi, kus saab muuta "
#~ "iga slaidi <acronym>HTML</acronym>-lehekülje nime."

#~ msgid "<screeninfo>Setting the slide names</screeninfo>"
#~ msgstr "<screeninfo>Slaidinimede määramine</screeninfo>"

#~ msgid "<phrase>Setting the slide names</phrase>"
#~ msgstr "<phrase>Slaidinimede määramine</phrase>"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "If your presentation was intended to be displayed in an unattended manner "
#~ "(&ie; automatic advance to next slide, &etc;), you can also make your "
#~ "<acronym>HTML</acronym> presentation counterpart exhibit the same "
#~ "behavior:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Kui sinu esitlus on mõeldud automaatseks esitamiseks (&ie; automaatsed "
#~ "üleminekud järgmistele slaididele &etc;), siis võid ka esitluse "
#~ "<acronym>HTML</acronym>-variandi automatiseerida:"

#~ msgid "<screeninfo>Unattended presentations</screeninfo>"
#~ msgstr "<screeninfo>Esitluste automatiseerimine</screeninfo>"

#~ msgid "<phrase>Unattended presentations</phrase>"
#~ msgstr "<phrase>Esitluste automatiseerimine</phrase>"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Here, you can force the slide to advance to the next after a specified "
#~ "amount of time, and also make the presentation return to the start once "
#~ "it reaches the end."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Siin saab määrata, et ühelt slaidilt teisele liigutakse automaatselt "
#~ "pärast teatud ajavahemikku, samuti selle, et lõppu jõudes naaseb esitlus "
#~ "taas oma alguspunkti."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Now it is time to actually produce your <acronym>HTML</acronym> "
#~ "presentation, the progress of which is shown in this dialog box:"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Nüüd ongi käes aeg <acronym>HTML</acronym>-esitlus tegelikult luua. Selle "
#~ "edenemist näeb järgmises dialoogis:"

#~ msgid "<screeninfo>Saving your configuration</screeninfo>"
#~ msgstr "<screeninfo>Konfiguratsiooni salvestamine</screeninfo>"

#~ msgid "<phrase>Saving your configuration</phrase>"
#~ msgstr "<phrase>Konfiguratsiooni salvestamine</phrase>"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Finally, you can save the configuration you have just used before you "
#~ "close the dialog box by pressing the <guibutton>Save Configuration...</"
#~ "guibutton> button."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Lõpuks salvesta enne dialoogi sulgemist seadistused, klõpsates selleks "
#~ "nupul <guibutton>Salvesta konfiguratsioon...</guibutton>"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Exporting &kpresenter; presentations to a <trademark>Memory Stick</"
#~ "trademark>"
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "&kpresenter;i esitluse eksportimine Sony mälupulgale (<trademark>Memory "
#~ "Stick</trademark>)"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Some Sony projectors have the ability to run a presentation directly from "
#~ "a <trademark>Memory Stick</trademark>, without needing to connect a "
#~ "computer up to the projector. &kpresenter; can export presentations to "
#~ "the format required by these projectors, and this tutorial will show you "
#~ "how to export your presentation."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Mõned Sony projektorid suudavad esitlust näidata ka otse mälupulgalt ilma "
#~ "arvutiga ühenduses olematagi. &kpresenter; võib esitlused vajalikku "
#~ "vormingusse eksportida, et mälupulka oleks võimalik selliselt kasutada. "
#~ "Allpool tutvustamegi eksportimise käiku."

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Each exported slideshow consists of a series of image files (one for each "
#~ "slide in the original presentation, plus two title slides) and an index "
#~ "file. They are created in a fairly complex folder structure that allows "
#~ "more than one presentation to be stored on a single memory stick. A "
#~ "simple example is shown below, consisting of two presentations."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Iga eksporditud slaidiseanss koosneb mitmest pildifailist (üks iga "
#~ "originaalesitluse slaidi kohta ning kaks tiitlislaidi) ja indeksifailist. "
#~ "Need luuakse suhteliselt keeruka kataloogistruktuuriga, mis võimaldab "
#~ "ühele mälupulgale salvestada ka enam kui ühe esitluse. Allpool toome ühe "
#~ "lihtsama, kahe esitlusega näite."

#~ msgid "<trademark>Memory Stick</trademark> folder structure"
#~ msgstr "Mälupulga kataloogistruktuur"

